<subSubSection lastPageId="29" pageId="28" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="28.[685,1172,372,1137]" pageId="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,820,1063,1084]" pageId="28">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2014" box="[1019,1092,1062,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pujoliclerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidus">
<emphasis box="[1019,1092,1062,1083]" italics="true" pageId="28">pallidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= pale) is a Latin adjective and refers to the predominantly yellow color of this beetle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[759,1098,1173,1196]" box="[759,1098,1173,1196]" pageId="28">
